s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:51:"Telephone number that the sender entered is invalid";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:76;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"10171";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"b1772f630efef6842fa8cea5b65e6c38";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:32:"The telephone number is invalid.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:77;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13458";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"fd6c11f271e7faa4b921122d984b4940";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:8:"Overview";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:78;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13459";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"b19a78247936d588751be9ac139fb86b";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:305:"On this screen, you can manage contact forms provided by Contact Form 7. You can manage an unlimited number of contact forms. Each contact form has a unique ID and Contact Form 7 shortcode ([contact-form-7 ...]). To insert a contact form into a post or a text widget, insert the shortcode into the target.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:79;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13460";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"9b37ca1ff888857fe120aeeb21dfc3af";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:154:"Hovering over a row in the contact forms list will display action links that allow you to manage your contact form. You can perform the following actions:";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:80;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13461";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"ea76c2469f54366347c0d04fef3cec30";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:148:"<strong>Edit</strong> - Navigates to the editing screen for that contact form. You can also reach that screen by clicking on the contact form title.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:81;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13462";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"b6e099df716ba84aada7287dc8cc23f6";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:140:"<strong>Duplicate</strong> - Clones that contact form. A cloned contact form inherits all content from the original, but has a different ID.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:82;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13463";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"d64bcf4d957d8dafed61478b3251ca01";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:101:"On this screen, you can edit a contact form. A contact form is comprised of the following components:";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:83;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13464";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"c5ed9c58ac7509b05ae78d439c77a948";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:126:"<strong>Title</strong> is the title of a contact form. This title is only used for labeling a contact form, and can be edited.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:84;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13465";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"5880875d721835f16410b86d5cd8c14b";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:172:"<strong>Form</strong> is a content of HTML form. You can use arbitrary HTML, which is allowed inside a form element. You can also use Contact Form 7&#8217;s form-tags here.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:85;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13466";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"74eac5df9f32c130fc7f777145142e33";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:178:"<strong>Mail</strong> manages a mail template (headers and message body) that this contact form will send when users submit it. You can use Contact Form 7&#8217;s mail-tags here.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:86;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13467";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"322cb620832476ea07856f78699980a3";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:168:"<strong>Mail (2)</strong> is an additional mail template that works similar to Mail. Mail (2) is different in that it is sent only when Mail has been sent successfully.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:87;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13468";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"2ee2f112f68da8d90881ff028fcf5cad";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:221:"In <strong>Messages</strong>, you can edit various types of messages used for this contact form. These messages are relatively short messages, like a validation error message you see when you leave a required field blank.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:88;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13469";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"e2e610466e43a4c2aafbb91a66c2d2b1";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:136:"<strong>Additional Settings</strong> provides a place where you can customize the behavior of this contact form by adding code snippets.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:89;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13470";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"b1969d732ba400a04aa90bfb6c1e962b";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:398:"A form-tag is a short code enclosed in square brackets used in a form content. A form-tag generally represents an input field, and its components can be separated into four parts: type, name, options, and values. Contact Form 7 supports several types of form-tags including text fields, number fields, date fields, checkboxes, radio buttons, menus, file-uploading fields, CAPTCHAs, and quiz fields.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:90;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13471";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"1abe194b2bd158d6c5a1372abf8f7d2e";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:218:"While form-tags have a comparatively complex syntax, you don&#8217;t need to know the syntax to add form-tags because you can use the straightforward tag generator (<strong>Generate Tag</strong> button on this screen).";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:91;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13472";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"64b230e8e0b79669dc0a20ced17e0ce7";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:203:"A mail-tag is also a short code enclosed in square brackets that you can use in every Mail and Mail (2) field. A mail-tag represents a user input value through an input field of a corresponding form-tag.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:92;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13473";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"31d8d53e900bbbaf4ad328ce81d17782";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:230:"There are also special mail-tags that have specific names, but don&#8217;t have corresponding form-tags. They are used to represent meta information of form submissions like the submitter&#8217;s IP address or the URL of the page.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:93;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13474";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"4aa6b549538b6d0b009bdb01a0ae00c0";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:160:"On this screen, you can manage services that are available through Contact Form 7. Using API will allow you to collaborate with any services that are available.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:94;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13475";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"ab3df08afc2ca1b290d81243de7b3ae2";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:183:"You may need to first sign up for an account with the service that you plan to use. When you do so, you would need to authorize Contact Form 7 to access the service with your account.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:95;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13476";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"1cb37c99ceb86b6bb955208418a905d4";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:97:"Any information you provide will not be shared with service providers without your authorization.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:96;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13477";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"da885e7d3a16dc303c0f8c9a19c15e6c";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:17:"Available Actions";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:97;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13478";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"fe3d0c24609149b20a0c8125e42e3df6";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:21:"For more information:";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:98;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13479";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"bc52b998d4fb1fa37be97b93ab04745e";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:29:"http://contactform7.com/docs/";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:99;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13480";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"ae443ff1a21bea4001d68b524db7d854";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:4:"Docs";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:100;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13481";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"4edf911925ce26fb30d355e5ccdd9c8c";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:28:"http://contactform7.com/faq/";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:101;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13482";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"dcffbeca5cad05eca992da911713b4f9";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:3:"FAQ";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:102;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13483";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"2bef58d36288b6aa31fc260db4178f9a";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:32:"http://contactform7.com/support/";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:103;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13484";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"9a81216513ce6d8f9d0128c23acfb914";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:7:"Support";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:104;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13485";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"b167e9075e395acdd2cbbec8eeb4348b";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:70:"The changes you made will be lost if you navigate away from this page.";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:105;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13486";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"ef90a7e47eca2b83e8e0de8bcfe04112";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:20:"How to correct this?";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:106;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13487";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"1c35ec5aa13617c16e5f7555f9bd401a";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:5:"Title";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:107;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13488";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"9c247ac6575a4a461f3e7cb51b1bf77c";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:9:"Shortcode";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:108;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13489";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"41b9f0d8ea14e379975963c6e88967aa";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:6:"Author";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i:109;O:8:"stdClass":6:{s:2:"id";s:5:"13490";s:6:"status";N;s:3:"ctx";s:32:"12b780c3f9b7b9ea577e83e1bafc5b98";s:10:"translated";N;s:8:"original";s:4:"Date";s:15:"gettext_context";s:0:"";}i